# GitHub push (agent)

Repo: **david9up/miditracker** · remote **origin**

## When pushing or using `gh`

1. Run git/gh commands with **full shell permissions** (not sandboxed) — sandbox blocks `github.com` DNS and SSH agent.
2. Prefer **`gh`** for GitHub tasks when available (`gh auth status` must succeed).
3. Never commit secrets (`.env`, tokens, PAT files). Never update global git config.

## Push workflow

```bash
cd /Users/davidmalcher/Projects/miditracker
git status -sb
git push origin main          # or feature branch
git push origin <tag>         # after releases
```

If SSH fails in agent but works for the user, retry with HTTPS (after `gh auth setup-git`):

```bash
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/david9up/miditracker.git
git push origin main
```

## Helper script

```bash
./scripts/push-to-github.sh [branch]
```

Runs pre-push checks (optional) and pushes with `gh` auth context.

## Pages deploy

Pushing to **main** triggers **Deploy GitHub Pages** workflow. No manual deploy unless workflow failed.

## One-time human setup

See **GITHUB_SETUP.md** — requires `gh auth login` once on this Mac.
